# Trivy ignore file — justified exceptions only.
# Format: CVE-YYYY-NNNNN  # <justification> — <owner> — <review date>
#
# Policy (framework §12.3):
# - Only CVEs with no upstream fix AND a documented compensating control may
#   live here. Anything with a fix upstream must be remediated, not ignored.
# - Each entry MUST be reviewed quarterly. Expired entries are dropped.
# - Base-image CVEs (Debian) are fixed by `apt-get upgrade` in the Dockerfile,
#   not by adding lines here.
#
# Add entries only via PR with security review.
